<p>In world of tri hedral objects, we could identify above junctions (and they are not only ones)</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>A fold is a line where 2 surfaces meet.</strong> </li>
<li>In a Y junction, each line is a fold</li>
<li>Important property of Y: If one is a fold, then through same reasoning other lines also should be fold</li>
<li><strong>A blade is a line wherew e cannot infer 2 surfaces are getting connected.</strong></li>
<li>There could be more formulation for L, but we are keeping simple here. </li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>In speech, we follow similar constraints. </li>
